3) \space
 \lim_{x\to 1}\; {1+ \sqrt{x}}=2
f'(1)
f(x)=\sqrt{x}
\lim_{x\to 1}\frac{1-\sqrt{x}}{1-x}=\lim_{x\to 1}\frac{\sqrt{x}-1}{x-1}
x=u^2
\quad
x = u^2\,.\quad 
x\to 1,\;\;u^2\to 1\implies u\to 1
 \lim_{x\to 1}\; \frac{1-x}{1- \sqrt{x}} \;\;=\;\; \lim_{u\to 1}\; \frac{1-u^2}{1- u} = \lim_{x\to 1} \frac{u^2 - 1}{u-1} \;=\;\lim_{u \to 1} \frac{(u-1)(u+1)}{u-1} = \lim_{u\to 1}(u + 1)  = 2
